  "prompt": "What is the Golden Gate bridge named after?",
  "response": "The Golden Gate Bridge is named after the Golden Gate Strait, the entrance to San Francisco Bay from the Pacific Ocean. The strait was named by U.S. Army Captain John C. Fr\u00e9mont in 1846, who likened it to the Golden Horn in Istanbul, Turkey. The name reflects the strait's significance as a major maritime route and its picturesque appearance.",
